<font color="#FF0000">ABOUT THIS SITE</font><br>
<tt>Fri Dec 19 15:14:03 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I discovered this site only a month or so ago, and was confused, shocked and dismayed at the conflict going on in the various threads. This site has such potential for healing.  I had almost given up hope when I logged on today and saw the tremendous outpouring of concern, support and love in the notes to and from Doc Del and Regina. This the real stuff! I will continue to monitor the site and respond as seems appropriate.  I served with the 9th Infantry Div out of Ben Luc for 4 months in 1970, severely wounded on July 9(lost a leg, etc, but not my sense of humor), spent a month at the 24th Evac in Long Binh, 3 months at Tachikawa AF Hosp in Japan, and 14 months at Fitzsimmons in Denver. I am in the process of retiring from various jobs, most recently as a prosthetist, due to increased symptoms of PTSD and Hepatitis C. Would love to communicate with others who spent time in those same areas. Thank to all for sharing your messages of hope and encouragement. We all benefit!<br>

<p><code>-- dorseydog@mail.brainerdonline.com  (Dan Kadlec) </code><p>


